place.name: STROXTON
place.gazetteerText: STROXTON, a parish in Grantham district, Lincoln; 3½ miles S by W of Grantham r. station. Post town, Grantham. Acres, 970. Real property, £1,547. Pop., 107. Houses, 22. The manor belongs to Sir G. E. Welby, Bart. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Lincoln. Value, £306.* Patron, Sir G. E. Welby. Bart. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
